Rule Learning, Probabilistic Methods. 

Rule Learning is present in the text as the paper advocates for the use of decision table classifiers, which are a type of rule-based classifier. The paper describes several algorithms for learning decision tables and compares their performance. 

Probabilistic Methods are also present in the text as the paper mentions Bayesian networks as one of the hypothesis spaces that machine learning researchers have concentrated on. However, the paper argues that decision table classifiers are more comprehensible for business users compared to these foreign hypothesis spaces.
